                    <msContents>

                        <summary>A <title>Grahaṇamālā</title> beginning with an eclipse in Śaka
                                <date type="Śaka">1769</date> (<date type="gregorian">1847</date>)
                            and ending with an eclipse in Śaka <date type="Śaka">1790</date> (<date
                                type="gregorian">1868</date>, containing twenty six eclipses in all,
                            both lunar and solar. The information includes: year (Śaka); full or new
                            moon; time of tithi; nakṣatra and its time; yoga and its time; weekday
                            and its time; month; duration; times of impact and release; whether
                            solar or lunar.</summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="sa">Sanskrit</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="Alpha_379">
                            <title>Grahaṇamālā</title>

                            <note>On <locus>F.1v</locus> is an astrological interpretation of an
                                eclipse that occured in Āśvina of Śaka <date type="Śaka">1779</date>
                                    (<date type="gregorian">September-October 1857</date>)during the
                                Indian Rebellion of 1857.</note>

                        </msItem>

